The paper deals with constructing differentially private synopses for geospatial datasets, which involves techniques from database systems (cs.DB) and privacy (cs.CR). The paper also discusses partitioning methods, which is a common technique in data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper proposes an adaptive-grid method, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.AI) to determine the partitioning of cells.
